<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870416-0040 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Inland Steel Industries Inc.</HL><DD> 04/16/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> IADEARNINGS (ERN) </IN><TEXT>   INLAND STEEL INDUSTRIES INC. reported first-quarter net income of $62.5 million, or $2.02 a share, compared with a $22 million loss in the year-earlier period. Sales rose 12% to $842.6 million from $754.1 million. The latest earnings largely reflected an extraordinary credit of $50 million from the refund of 50% of the Chicago company's accumulated investment tax credits. Under the 1986 federal tax law, steel companies can receive cash for half their deferred credits if they agree to give up the other half. </TEXT></DOC>